org.dataconservancy.packaging.gui.presenter.impl

Class PackageDescriptionPresenterImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.dataconservancy.packaging.gui.presenter.impl.BasePresenterImpl
      • org.dataconservancy.packaging.gui.presenter.impl.PackageDescriptionPresenterImpl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    EventListener, PreferenceChangeListener, PackageDescriptionPresenter, Presenter

    public class PackageDescriptionPresenterImpl
extends BasePresenterImpl
implements PackageDescriptionPresenter, PreferenceChangeListener
    Implementation for the presenter that displays the package description tree. Handles generation of the tree, changing types of artifacts, sorting tree elements, validating the package description, and saving the changed package description.

      • findInvalidProperties

        public List<String> findInvalidProperties(org.dataconservancy.packaging.tool.model.PackageArtifact packageArtifact,
                                          String type)
        Description copied from interface: PackageDescriptionPresenter
        Goes through all the artifacts in the package description and finds any properties that aren't valid. This can occur when a property has been set and then artifact type has change, and the previously set property doesn't exist on the new type.
        Specified by:
        findInvalidProperties in interface PackageDescriptionPresenter
        Parameters:
        packageArtifact - the package description to look for invalid properties
        type - The type to check the properties of the artifact against, if you want to test if the artifact has invalid properties pass it's current type.
        Returns:
        A map of strings with properties that are invalid keyed by the artifact, maybe empty but never null.
